<h2><a name=3D"_Toc228569151">World Generator System</a> </h2>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>This is the PCG known as the world generator system, w=
hich
uses PCG algorithms, specifically Perlin, <span class=3DSpellE>Cnoise</span=
>, <span
class=3DSpellE>Snoise</span> noise generators to procedurally generate terr=
ain,
terrain heightmaps, biome texturing, and the placement of enemies and
obstacles. The Start() method initialises references to the <span class=3DS=
pellE>GameManager</span>,
the Unity Terrain <span class=3DSpellE>obastcles</span>, and the <span
class=3DSpellE>NavMeshSurface</span>, ensuring the generator has access to =
all
the required systems it needs to perform. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>The script provides several methods such as <span
class=3DSpellE>GetTerrainObject</span>() exposes the generated terrain to t=
he
other systems, <span class=3DSpellE>GetWorldIsReady</span>() allows the game
manager to synchronise gameplay with the world generation, and <span
class=3DSpellE>BakeNavigation</span>() rebuilds the <span class=3DSpellE>Na=
vMesh</span>
after the terrain has been modified. </p>

